description:
A web application has a 'ping' utility that takes an IP address as input:

```php
$ip = $_GET['ip'];
system("ping -c 4 " . $ip);
```

The input is concatenated directly into a shell command without sanitization.

Craft a payload that will also run `cat /etc/passwd` after the ping command.

Submit the separator character you'd use: flag{separator}

Hint: You need a shell metacharacter that says 'run this next command regardless'
